        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Avoid retaining menu refresh state",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Avoid retaining `StatusItemController` and the open menu for the full Codex account-scoped refresh task.\n- Capture the long-lived `UsageStore` and `SettingsStore` for the async refresh, while keeping the controller/menu weak in phase-change callbacks.\n- Add a regression test that releases the status controller while an account-scoped refresh is blocked in flight.\n\n## Proof\nFocused proof rerun locally on June 17, 2026 PT at head `093da38c`.\n\n`swift test --filter StatusMenuCodexSwitcherTests`:\n\n```text\nTest \"codex account scoped refresh does not retain status controller while in flight\" passed after 0.109 seconds.\nSuite StatusMenuCodexSwitcherTests passed after 1.418 seconds.\nTest run with 22 tests in 1 suite passed after 1.418 seconds.\n```\n\n`.build/lint-tools/bin/swiftlint --strict Sources/CodexBar/StatusItemController+Menu.swift Tests/CodexBarTests/StatusMenuCodexSwitcherTests.swift`:\n\n```text\nDone linting! Found 0 violations, 0 serious in 2 files.\n```\n\n`swift build --build-tests`:\n\n```text\nBuild complete! (1.41 sec)\n```\n\n`git diff --check`: passed.\n\n## Notes\n- This is intentionally separate from the logging performance PR.\n",
